modules.description: This module defines a JSON data model with values supporting null, boolean, number, string, array, and object types. It provides bidirectional conversion between JSON values and S-expressions, along with comparison and hashing for structured data. It is used for parsing, manipulating, and serializing JSON data in a type-safe manner.

This module defines a type `t` representing JSON values with variants for objects, arrays, primitives, and more. It provides functions to convert between JSON values and S-expressions, compare JSON values, and compute their hash. Use this module to parse, manipulate, and serialize JSON data directly, such as processing API responses or configuration files.

This module provides functions to parse, manipulate, and serialize JSON data using two distinct JSON data models. Each submodule represents JSON values with algebraic data types and supports conversions to and from S-expressions, along with comparison and hash operations. Concrete use cases include processing API responses, reading configuration files, and handling structured data in a type-safe manner.
